✅ Steps to Create "Hello World" Jenkins Job
Login to Jenkins.

Click on “New Item” from the left menu.

Enter a name: HelloWorld

Select Freestyle project, then click OK.

Scroll down to Build section → Click "Add build step" → Select "Execute shell" (Linux) or "Execute Windows batch command" (Windows).

In the command box, type:
echo "Hello World"
Click Save.

Click Build Now.

To see the output: Go to Build History → Click the build → Console Output
  ✅ Output:
Started by user admin
Building in workspace /var/lib/jenkins/workspace/HelloWorld
Hello World
Finished: SUCCESS
